sessing whether any extra configuration is necessary before moving forward with the testing process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"jackrabbit-webdav exposes servlet-facing WebDAV server/request/response APIs, while its Maven POM declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as provided; meaningful tests that touch those APIs need the servlet API on the test compile/runtime classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The library is a WebDAV server/client utility library with classes such as servlet wrappers and WebDAV request/response contexts that reference javax.servlet types, but the artifact does not bring servlet-api transitively because it is provided-scope. The existing scaffold for 1.5.0 already adds this dependency.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property setup is indicated. Prefer in-process tests of WebDAV method objects, XML parsing/serialization, report registration, locator factories, and servlet-facing classes using lightweight test doubles rather than requiring an external Jackrabbit webapp or WebDAV server.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact is old and beta-versioned, so APIs may differ slightly from the existing 1.5.0 tests; local Gradle and native-image verification remain authoritative.\",\n    \"SLF4J may emit warnings without a binding, but that is not concrete evidence that a binding is required for meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0539e7fb1070c5d1016a428c65115081978c78800612a0fe67\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1804, "output": 833, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36429, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 